  <p>Overwhelmingly reliant on the lobster export, Maine lost nearly 85 percent of its usual export to the Chinese market in 2018. In 2017, the US exported nearly 12 million pounds of live lobster, but a year after the tariffs, the number of exports declined by nearly 10 million pounds.The loss of business soon translated into the loss of jobs. Dealers like the Lobster Co., of Arundel laid off half of the wholesale staff.
   <p>In September 2017, the Canadians and the Europeans negotiated a comprehensive economic trade agreement, which eliminated tariffs imposed lobster coming from Canada to the EU. This preferential trade agreement has already been in effect when the retaliatory tariffs by China were announced a year later.</p> 

